{
  "texts": [
    "One measure of stability is the standard deviation of the results from the 5 repeats of 5-fold cross-validation.",
    "These values are shown in brackets in Supplementary Table S6 online.",
    "For the ADNI data set, the standard deviation of the results is generally in the range 0.01 to 0.02, which is quite low.",
    "Many models achieved the minimum standard deviation of 0.01.",
    "For the MAS data set, on the other hand, the minimum standard deviation of 0.04 was achieved by sequential forward selection on the Cox model with gradient boosting."
  ]
}